The paper discusses a new algorithm for cylindrical algebraic decompositions (CADs) and focuses on problem formulation for input to this algorithm. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Symbolic Computation (cs.SC). The algorithm also involves constructing a complex decomposition by refining a tree incrementally by constraint, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Computational Geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses heuristics for making choices about the order in which constraints are presented, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper involves developing new heuristics, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
